cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a new approach to train Generative Adversarial Nets (GANs) with multiple generators to overcome the mode collapsing problem. The paper focuses on the application of this approach to natural image databases, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also includes theoretical analysis and experimental results, which suggest that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
